<p></p>
<p>With brother&rsquo;s help, DB has successed in flirt with TN. (see <a href="http://spoj.com/problems/QTNOEL">QTNOEL</a>). But now he has another problem :</p>
<p>In Vietnamese Tet holidays (Vietnam&rsquo;s Lunar New Year), there is a custom called &lsquo;Li xi&rsquo; that adult give children money in red packs, to wish them strong and happy. DB&rsquo;s family has a very special method to give children Li xi :</p>
<p>There are n Li xi packs, every pack has a[i] VND &ndash; Vietnamese unit of money, and a random positive integer k (1 &le; k &le; n). DB can take any pack, but mustn&rsquo;t take k packs in a row.</p>
<p>Let&rsquo;s help him to find the way to take the maximum of money.</p>
<p><strong>Input :</strong></p>
<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; First line : two integer n and k</p>
<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Second line : n integer, the i-th number is a[i]</p>
<p><strong>Output :</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A single number s &ndash; the maximum money DB can take.</p>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Input:</strong></p>
<p>5 3</p>
<p>6 19 8 7 13</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong></p>
<p>45</p>
<p><strong>Limit :</strong></p>
<p>- 0 &le; a[i] &le; 2000</p>
<p>- n &le; 10<sup>6</sup></p>
<p> </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

